<br>
Point 1 is basically that Mythic doesn't want you to take up server resources unless you are actively playing the game.  However, alt-tabbing out and back in is no different than going AFK, or doing something else while your character stands or sits there in the game (e.g., read a book, watch TV, etc.).   While I understand the business and financial motive here, it has nothing to do with "cheating."<br>
<br>
And while I agree that you shouldn't be running other applications that take up your comp resources while playing DAoC because it can impact the performance of the game for you, if you are alt-tabbing out, that's not really a concern, is it?<br>
<br>
BTW, if they want to get rid of "sitting in our game taking up our server's cycles and bandwidth that other, more active players could put to better use," then they ought to make horses run faster...much faster. <br>
<br>
