If I were Mythic and had a bit of common sense, I would look at all the bitterness towards the other MMRPG game companies and try to come out as the good guy.  That means compromising my (Mythic's) position where it's a feature the consumer wants and would have no practical effect on gameplay or the bottom line.<br>
