<br>
They created the client they way they thought would reduce cracking and cheating. If alt-tab is blocked to prevent that, then you either suck it back and deal with it or quit playing. Feel the need to attempt a class action? Like I said, go talk to a lawyer, you'll get laughed right out of his office. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/9/01 5:31:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ;)</span><hr size=1> EQAquinas says:  <b><i>So do you think that Mythic has a valid reason for cancelling your account if they just don't like selling you the game any more?</b></i><br>
<br>
Yes.  For example, if sales were low and they decided to discontinue the service, they wouldn't be acting in bad faith.  Or, if they decided to cut 10% of their play base (randomly chosen) to reduce costs, they wouldn't be acting in bad faith.  Hence, no double standard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqaquinas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQAquinas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/9/01 8:31:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt-tab (background) functionality restored</span><hr size=1> Scirocco: We'd best just agree to disagree.  Case citations on the Druids Grove message board are a sure sign that things have gotten out of hand. :)<br>
