<br>
Huh?  I am neither playing at work, nor a cracker, and it affects me.  I like to listen to music while I play games.  If I want to change the song that's playing, I can't alt-tab out to do so.  If I want to use an instant messenger during my downtime, I can't.  If I accidentally hit the windows key, minimizing DAoC, I'm screwed.  There is a plethora of legitimate uses for alt-tabbing; just because you don't have any doesn't mean that no one does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/10/01 2:40:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt-tab (background) functionality restored</span><hr size=1> Um, Griif, lots of people use their computers for things other than getting info about a game they're playing on it.  Given the fact that the game does have down time, or that circumstances frequently arise where you need to turn your attention to other things briefly (e.g., your spouse asks you to check to see if an email has come in), then alt-tabbing out and in is certainly legitimate.  <br>
